DESCRIPTION:
  - Subset of Sonoran Cellular web application.

DEFAULT FILES:
  - README_hw8
  - destroy.sql
  - create.sql
  - populate.sql
  - LoginServlet.java
  - AddPlan.java
  - AddAccountInformation.java
  - FindBill.java
  - OracleConnect.java
  - SharedAssigment.jsp

EXTRA FILES:
  - main.js
  - draw.js
  - shared_plan.js
  - jquery.min.js
  - style.css

DEPENDENCIES:
  - java 7
  - oracle jdbc driver
  - sqlpl
  - modern browser capable of javascript!

COMPILING:
  $ cd SonoranCellular/WEB-INF/classes
  $ make

USAGE:
  in browser:
  oxford:3868/SonoranCellular/

NOTES:
  - It does not say to turnin OracleConnect.java, but we added many functions
    to that file which are necessary for our web application, so we turned it in
  - the files main.js, draw.js and jquery.min.js all should be in the root of
    SonoranCellular/ directory.
  - We did not edit the Makefile

EXTRA CREDIT:

  1) additional functionality: dynamic web content
      -- we used javascript ajax calls to submit forms, and captured the return
         values from our servlets. Then we updated the html in current page,
         or gave the user a popup alert message.  ie, we returned either
         JSON objects or text from the servlet instead of html and dynamically
         generated html content in the current page using javascript.

  2) professional look: web design styling
      -- style.css defines the styling for the page content. We used this to
         make the site look more professional, and the html more readable.

